<span id="freeTextContainer8746224460327308736">Good book. It’s a different look at the Civil War through the lens of death. It covers all aspects of death and how the war either changed trends or magnified thereof. It’s an interesting and fresh look at a war that has otherwise been picked over to death. The writing is readable and sympathetic to the subject. It helps that the quotations are short and to the point. The analysis seems sound enough. That said, it does seem like a time capsule, there aren’t many lessons to draw for today. Times </span>
  <span id="freeText8746224460327308736" style="display:none">Good book. It’s a different look at the Civil War through the lens of death. It covers all aspects of death and how the war either changed trends or magnified thereof. It’s an interesting and fresh look at a war that has otherwise been picked over to death. The writing is readable and sympathetic to the subject. It helps that the quotations are short and to the point. The analysis seems sound enough. That said, it does seem like a time capsule, there aren’t many lessons to draw for today. Times and technology have simply changed too much to really connect unless one served or has family who served and fought in battle. Well worth reading if you like war history. <br /> </span>
