<div id="review_2337966612" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2337966612" />
    <a title="Babbs" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4492706-babbs"><img alt="Babbs" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623793861p2/4492706.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2337966612?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Babbs" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Babbs" href="/user/show/4492706-babbs">Babbs</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8133793-this-republic-of-suffering">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4492706-babbs?shelf=history_based">history_based</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4492706-babbs?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4492706-babbs?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4492706-babbs?shelf=military-combat-war">military-combat-war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2337966612" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11740511775920050170"><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“It is hard,” he wrote, “to realize the meaning of the figures…It is easy to imagine one man killed; or ten men killed; or, perhaps, a score of men killed…but even…[the veteran] is unable to comprehend the dire meaning of the one hundred thousand, whose every unit represents a soldier’s bloody grave. The figures are too large.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br/>The way this book is broken down, from Dying versus Killing, to Naming of those lost, sections off different aspects of the war, and the impact it had not only</span>
  <span id="freeText11740511775920050170" style="display:none"><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“It is hard,” he wrote, “to realize the meaning of the figures…It is easy to imagine one man killed; or ten men killed; or, perhaps, a score of men killed…but even…[the veteran] is unable to comprehend the dire meaning of the one hundred thousand, whose every unit represents a soldier’s bloody grave. The figures are too large.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br />The way this book is broken down, from Dying versus Killing, to Naming of those lost, sections off different aspects of the war, and the impact it had not only on the soldiers who fought it, but on their families and the country as a whole. Constructed mostly as a chronological narrative, with quotes from ledgers, newspapers, and personal letters as examples, this is one of the most human accounts of war that I've ever read. I also enjoyed the expansion that included the impact of literary works on the public's perception of the war and the consequences that came from the greatest lost of American life to date. <br /><br />This would be an excellent starting point for anyone interested in reading more about the Civil War and I personally plan on following up on several of the authors of the time, specifically Longfellow and Whitman. <br /><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>"That fatal bullet went speeding forth <br />Till it reached a town in the distant North <br />Till it reached a house in a sunny street <br />Till it reached a heart that ceased to beat <br />Without a murmur, without a cry …….….….…. <br />And the neighbors wondered that she should die."</b>
  </i>
</blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="11740511775920050170" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


