        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2415601468" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12054316348572595295">While the sub-title of the book indicates the focus on the Civil War, much of what Faust illustates can be applied to how cheaply we seem to hold life these days. And no, I&apos;m not talking soley about inner city violence, but mass shootings, terrorist attacks. You name it. Because, the book is about how society&apos;s view to death changed radically during the Civil War.<br/><br/>Faust&apos;s book is divided into chapters, each named with a facet of death. She details the original view of death in the society of the </span>
  <span id="freeText12054316348572595295" style="display:none">While the sub-title of the book indicates the focus on the Civil War, much of what Faust illustates can be applied to how cheaply we seem to hold life these days. And no, I'm not talking soley about inner city violence, but mass shootings, terrorist attacks. You name it. Because, the book is about how society's view to death changed radically during the Civil War.<br /><br />Faust's book is divided into chapters, each named with a facet of death. She details the original view of death in the society of the time, but then how that changed with the war - not only in terms of how the army dealt with the bodies of the wounded, but also how individuals dealt with the missing loved ones. It is an enthralling and distrubing read that is a needed one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12054316348572595295" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
